<p>This is a consequence of pension reform passed in 2012. As usual, the pain was back loaded almost 10 years out and school district operating budgets will see as much as ~20% of their funds diverted to retiree pensions and healthcare. Declining enrollments exacerbate this problem as does diversion to charter schools. I wonder if the messy pension finances will also get an airing if more transparency is demanded.</p>
